=== LAB 01.2: (Installing Centos/Review)

OBJECTIVE:

In this lab, you will practice to set up your own centos machine.
You will be using Virtual Machine Manager to set up a new virtual machine
 with a centos image.


SETUP:

Before beginning the lab, Please read ahead on Chapter 10 on the book and 
 Chapter 11 on the videos on Safari Online.

STEPS:

Log in to your Host Machine
  1. Open Virtual Machine Manager ( Type " virt-manager " on terminal ).
  2. Create a new Virtual Manager Using the ISO image on the downloads folder 
     on your host machine and use the default settings on it.
    
Instructions for creating a virtual machine on virt-manager

  1. Run " virt-manager " on your terminal
  2. Click file > New Virtual Machine > Forward > Browse > Browse Local >
     Under Home > User > Downloads > Centos > Choose Volume 
  3. Use the default settings.

